<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2007-06-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Combined distemper-adenoviral pneumonia in a dog</TITLE><BODY>A 3 1/2-month-old pug with oculonasal discharge and seizures was submitted for postmortem examination. Grossly, the lungs had cranioventral consolidation, and microscopically, 2 distinct types of inclusion bodies compatible with Canine distemper virus and Canine adenovirus type 2. Presence of both viruses was confirmed via immunohistochemical staining.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>